                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Minimalist Bodywork: </span> The body panels are expected to be minimal and functional, designed to protect the internal components while keeping the bike's weight in check. Elements like a raised front beak, knuckle guards, and a high-set windscreen add to its adventure-ready persona. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Dual-purpose Tyres: </span>The bike is likely to feature wire-spoke wheels with dual-purpose tyres, which offer superior grip and durability on a variety of surfaces, from asphalt to gravel. </li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Advanced Lighting: </span> Just like OLA's other products, the Adventure will feature an all-LED lighting setup, which will not only enhance visibility but also give it a distinct, futuristic look. The headlamp will likely be a new, uniquely designed unit that fits the adventure theme. </li>
                </ul>
                <p>The design of the OLA Adventure is a clear indicator that it is built for a specific purpose: to explore. It's a machine that promises to be a reliable partner on any journey, regardless of the terrain. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Expected Price and Launch Timeline: The Journey Begins</h3>
                <p>The pricing of the OLA Adventure is a topic of much speculation. As a premium electric motorcycle, it is expected to be priced higher than most scooters but competitively against its petrol-powered rivals. Various reports suggest a price range, and based on the expected features and OLA's history of aggressive pricing, a realistic ex-showroom price is likely to fall between <span class="font-weight-700">₹1.5 lakh and ₹2 lakh. </span> Some sources even suggest a higher price point of up to <span class="font-weight-700">₹3 lakh</span>, which would place it in direct competition with established premium ADVs. </p>
                <p>As for the launch timeline, OLA has been a master of generating hype, and the wait for its motorcycles has been considerable. While initial concepts were shown in 2023, the company is now focused on bringing its electric motorcycles to market. The latest information points to an expected launch in<span class="font-weight-700"> October 2025. </span> This gives OLA enough time to refine the product, build out its charging infrastructure, and ensure a smooth rollout for a vehicle that will be a first of its kind in the Indian market. </p>
